                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/8660: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Greece</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacVeagh</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Athens</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-02-26T13:00:00+02:00"
                            >February 26, 1941—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received February 27—7:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>102. The Prime Minister told me this morning that he is “more than sure” that
                    German military occupation of Bulgaria will involve an attack on Greece. He said
                    that the Axis is finding the Albanian situation a “cancer” which cannot be cured
                    by the Italians alone and while no formal German demands have yet been made on
                    this country there have been plenty of indications that such may be expected to
                    which Greece will react exactly as she did to the Italian ultimatum. She will
                    resist alone if necessary but he feels sure the British will send help and that
                    Greek resistance will give them the time to do so. Furthermore, he believes that
                    Turkey’s obligations to Great Britain will bring her into the war under these
                    circumstances and added that news from Yugoslavia during the last few days has
                    been definitely encouraging.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacVeagh</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
